        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1243019946" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14697719866178398597">I picked this up on impulse at a used book sale, and then it took me forever to dip into it. It is unlike anything I&apos;ve ever read. I&apos;ve read the other reviews and don&apos;t think I&apos;d call it charming, as they did. Instead, I&apos;d say it was thought-provoking. I think I saw each of the7 capital sins in control of a villager, and I think they struggled to connect something they were doing with what dire things were happening to their island. Others may think I&apos;m crazy, but that&apos;s why (and not because of </span>
  <span id="freeText14697719866178398597" style="display:none">I picked this up on impulse at a used book sale, and then it took me forever to dip into it. It is unlike anything I've ever read. I've read the other reviews and don't think I'd call it charming, as they did. Instead, I'd say it was thought-provoking. I think I saw each of the7 capital sins in control of a villager, and I think they struggled to connect something they were doing with what dire things were happening to their island. Others may think I'm crazy, but that's why (and not because of the title) I put it on my religious book shelf.</span>
